[4, "Like many of the Paranormal Romance titles this is marketed as YA but can be found as easily among the adult novels, with characters, intrigue and pace of a high quality that sets the page-turning quotient on high (I read White Cat in one sitting). I would also say in passing that Gollancz cover (shown) is more fitting than the `Twilight' cover of the McElderry US edition. Red Glove, the second Curse Workers Book is expected May 2011.", [2, 4, 12, 29, 52], [0, 1, 8, 24, 26]]